        <section id="philosophy">
            <h1>Philosophy</h1>
            <ul>
                <li>Full support for HTML elements (and only HTML elements)</li>
                <li>Smart CSS rules for good out-of-the-box layout</li>
                <li>Wide support for base colors and patterns</li>
                <li>Opinionated but simple design rules</li>
                <li>Easy to overwrite when everything goes horribly wrong</li>
                <li>No grid, no columns, no components</li>
                <li>Don't call it a framework!</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="elements">
            <h1>Elements</h1>
            <main>
                <h2>Main</h2>
                <p>The main element includes a background color and the dots pattern by default. There's one at the top of this page, too.</p>
                <p>This is a main element. Like the immortals in <em>Highlander</em>, there should be only one of them.</p>
            </main>

            <h2>Sections</h2>
            <p>Use of the <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> element (seen throughout this page) is encouraged. Sections have default CSS for spacing out your content that's aimed at getting it looking good on the first pass.</p>

            <h2>Asides</h2>
            <p>Asides center everything inside them using flexbox.</p>
            <aside>This is an aside.</aside>
            <p>It's useful for buttons:</p>
            <aside><button class="reaction">I'm centered!</button><button class="failure">Me too</button></aside>

            <h2>Typography</h2>

            <p>Typography rules are applied directly to HTML elements.</p>

            <h3>Headlines</h3>
            <p>Pretty much what you'd expect. Headlines are centered by default but that's probably easy to change.</p>

            <h1>This is headline text. (h1)</h1>
            <h2>This is headline text. (h2)</h2>
            <h3>This is headline text. (h3)</h3>
            <h4>This is headline text. (h4)</h4>
            <h5>This is headline text. (h5)</h5>
            <h6>This is headline text. (h6)</h6>

            <h3>Blockquotes</h3>
            <blockquote>
                You may delay, but time will not.
                <cite>Benjamin Franklin</cite>
            </blockquote>

            <h3>Paragraphs, etc.</h3>
            <p>Paragraphs (like this one!) are by default limited to 50 characters width (or whatever <code>@text-measure</code> is set to). They have an aggressive, but not too aggressive, line height of 1.62 (also a variable!).</p>

            <h3>Figures</h3>
            <figure>
                <img src="http://placekitten.com/300/300" alt="A Kitten">
                <figcaption>This figcaption explains that this is an image of a kitten.</figcaption>
                <caption>A caption element would accomplish the same thing.</caption>
            </figure>

            <h3>Other Block Elements</h3>
            <article>
                <pre>This is pre-formatted text</pre>
                <p>Horizontal rule:</p>
                <hr>
            </article>

            <h3>Other Inline Elements</h3>
            <p>Paragraphs may also contain <abbr title="abbreviations, to the layperson">abbreves</abbr> and <acronym title="Aribitrarily Invented Acronyms For Display Purposes">AIAFDPS</acronym>.</p>
            <p>Sometimes you just need an <code>an inline code snippet</code>.</p>

        </section>
