        <section>
            <h1>LESS</h1>

            <p>Strapless offers some other handy LESS files, like:</p>

            <dl>
                <dt>mixins.less</dt>
                <dd>Mixins for handling text color issues and other LESSer issues.</dd>

                <dt>variables.less</dt>
                <dd>A very short variable file that you will never have to scroll through.</dd>

                <dt>targets.less</dt>
                <dd>Simple, reusable target mixins for handling responsiveness.</dd>

                <dt>colors.less</dt>
                <dd>Powerful, flexible color scheme generation.</dd>

                <dt>patterns.less</dt>
                <dd>Simple SVG-based color-shifting patterns ready to drop in to your project.</dd>

                <dt>normalize.less</dt>
                <dd><a href="http://www.github.com/necolas/normalize.css">Includes a great normalize file</a> to make your HTML and CSS work easier.</dd>
            </dl>

            

            <h2>Useful LESS variables</h2>
            <p>StrapLESS calculates some useful variables for your project:</p>
            <dl>
                <dt>@scheme-type</dt>
                <dd>Returns either <em>light</em>, <em>medium</em>, or <em>dark</em> depending on your base color.</dd>
                <dt>@success and @failure</dt>
                <dd>A well-paired successful green and failure red that work with your theme</dd>
                <dt>@info and @warning</dt>
                <dd>A calming blue and more urgent orange demarking information</dd>
                <dt>@action and @reaction</dt>
                <dd>A generic opposing pair of colors based on your project's @base-color</dd>
            </dl>

        </section>

